 ethnic name for a British Celt), or from the genitive plural of the tribal name, meaning ‘of the British’ + Old English <i>ford</i> ‘ford’."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Hebrew: Bitter; Marion is the French form."],"variants":[{"name":"Marion","meanings":["Originally a medieval French diminutive form of   Marie  , introduced to Britain in the Middle Ages. In some places it was taken as a pet form of   Margaret   or   Margery .  As a male name, it is an altered form of the Continental male name <i>Marian</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>Marianus</i> (from   Marius  ), but is now rarely, if ever, used. It was the birth name of the American film star  John Wayne  (  1907–79 )."]},{"name":"Marcia","meanings":["Often used as a feminine equivalent of   Mark  , but in fact a feminine form of <i>Marcius</i>, itself a derivative of   Marcus .  One  St Marcia  is commemorated in a group with Felix, Luciolus, Fortunatus, and others; another with Zenais, Cyria, and Valeria; and a third with Ariston, Crescentian, Eutychian, Urban, Vitalis, Justus, Felicissimus, Felix, and Symphorosa. None is individually very famous."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":1,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705197,"age":74,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Comberford was born in 1381, in Tamworth, Staffordshire, England. She married John Revell in 1401, in Liversedge, Yorkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in Liversedge, Yorkshire, England."},"et":{"1381–":"1381–Surnud","1378–Male":"1378–Surnud","1402–1490":"1402–1490","1381–Female":"1381–Surnud","1402":"1402","1401":"1401","1455":"1455","1378":"1378","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1490":"1490","Tamworth, Staffordshire, England":"Tamworth, Staffordshire, England","Liversedge, Yorkshire, England":"Liversedge, Yorkshire, England","Birstall, Yorkshire, England":"Birstall, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1381–":"1381–Kuollut","1378–Male":"1378–Kuollut","1402–1490":"1402–1490","1381–Female":"1381–Kuollut","1402":"1402","1401":"1401","1455":"1455","1378":"1378","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1490":"1490","Tamworth, Staffordshire, England":"Tamworth, Staffordshire, England","Liversedge, Yorkshire, England":"Liversedge, Yorkshire, England","Birstall, Yorkshire, England":"Birstall, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"1381–":"1381–Décédée","1378–Male":"1378–Décédé","1402–1490":"1402–1490","1381–Female":"1381–Décédée","1402":"1402","1401":"1401","1455":"1455","1378":"1378","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1490":"1490","Tamworth, Staffordshire, England":"Tamworth, Staffordshire, Angleterre","Liversedge, Yorkshire, England":"Liversedge, Everwyck, Angleterre","Birstall, Yorkshire, England":"Birstall, Everwyck, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mary Comberford est née en 1381, à Tamworth, Staffordshire, Angleterre. Elle a épousé John Revell en 1401, à Liversedge, Everwyck, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Elle est décédée à Liversedge, Everwyck, Angleterre."},"de":{"1381–":"1381–Verstorben","1378–Male":"1378–Verstorben","1402–1490":"1402–1490","1381–Female":"1381–Verstorben","1402":"1402","1401":"1401"